<TITLE> Russia`s Putin to attend NATO summit: RIA </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Moscow, Feb 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Russian President Vladimir Putin will attend a NATO summit in early April, Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov was quoted as saying by RIA news agency on Tuesday. "President Vladimir Putin has accepted an invitation to take part in the summit," the agency quoted Lavrov as saying during a visit to Geneva. "This yet again testifies to the fact that Russia is open to dialogue on any issues," Lavrov said.
